# Design — Fix rate_limit cooldown thrash + user-side override plumbing

## Architecture

Two-file structural change, plus tests. No new modules, no new state, no new event types.

### Change 1 — `src/types.ts:92-95`: extend `defaultConfig.cooldownMsByCategory`

```ts
cooldownMsByCategory: {
  quota_exhausted: 60 * 60_000, // 1 hour
  auth_error: 30 * 60_000, // 30 minutes
  rate_limit: 30 * 60_000, // 30 minutes — NEW
},
```

Update rationale comment (`types.ts:84-91`): drop `rate_limit` from the "transient categories" list; explain the new default reflects observed hour-scale provider windows (MiniMax Token Plan) while leaving room for user override.

**Documentation cleanup at the same site** (per validator finding): also update `types.ts:49-53` (warns about rate_limit-as-transient thrash — stale once rate_limit moves into the override map) and `types.ts:22-23` (mentions `.opencode/model-routing.json` which this change does NOT establish — keep reference but clarify tuple options are the canonical path; the `.opencode/model-routing.json` sibling remains out of scope).

### Change 2 — `src/plugin-internal.ts`: plumb `pluginOptions.cooldownMsByCategory` → `PluginConfig`

Three surgical edits in one file.

**2a. Exported typed extractor helper with prototype-safe exhaustiveness** (per validator pass-2 blocker — `s in obj` traverses prototype chain, must use `Object.hasOwn`; per validator pass-2 warning — extractor must be exported for direct unit testing):

```ts
// Compile-time-exhaustive category set: adding/removing an ErrorCategory
// member in types.ts fails this type-check, preventing drift.
const KNOWN_CATEGORIES = {
  rate_limit: true,
  server_error: true,
  unknown_model: true,
  auth_error: true,
  ttft_timeout: true,
  quota_exhausted: true,
  unknown: true,
} as const satisfies Record<ErrorCategory, true>;

// Prototype-safe membership check. `s in obj` would accept inherited names
// like "toString", "constructor", "__proto__" — Object.hasOwn does not.
// Per validator pass-2 blocker.
function isErrorCategory(s: string): s is ErrorCategory {
  return Object.hasOwn(KNOWN_CATEGORIES, s);
}

// Exported for direct unit testing (test/plugin.test.ts Change 3c).
// Extract and validate cooldownMsByCategory from pluginOptions. Defensive:
// malformed entries are dropped with a warning, never crash. Returns undefined
// when absent or entirely invalid — caller falls through to defaultConfig.
//
// Infinity handling: Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY is the documented "permanent
// block within process lifetime" sentinel (types.ts:55-56). It is accepted
// programmatically (tests, internal callers) but cannot be expressed in JSON
// configuration (RFC 8259 §6 forbids Infinity in JSON numbers) — users wishing
// permanent block must use a sufficiently large finite value (e.g., 10 years)
// or await a future JSON-representable sentinel contract (out of scope).
export function extractCooldownOverrides(
  pluginOptions: unknown,
  logger: Logger,
): Partial<Record<ErrorCategory, number>> | undefined {
  if (!isRecord(pluginOptions)) return undefined;
  const raw = (pluginOptions as { cooldownMsByCategory?: unknown }).cooldownMsByCategory;
  if (!isRecord(raw)) return undefined;
  const out: Partial<Record<ErrorCategory, number>> = {};
  for (const [k, v] of Object.entries(raw)) {
    if (!isErrorCategory(k)) {
      logger.warn("pluginOptions.cooldown.invalid_category", { category: k });
      continue;
    }
    // Accept finite non-negative numbers OR +Infinity (programmatic sentinel).
    // Reject NaN, -Infinity, negative, and non-number types.
    if (
      typeof v !== "number" ||
      Number.isNaN(v) ||
      v === Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY ||
      v < 0 ||
      !(Number.isFinite(v) || v === Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY)
    ) {
      logger.warn("pluginOptions.cooldown.invalid_value", { category: k, value: v });
      continue;
    }
    out[k] = v;
  }
  return Object.keys(out).length > 0 ? out : undefined;
}
```

**2b. Update `createPluginContext` with 3-layer merge** (per validator pass-1 compatibility finding — preserves defaults through every configuration layer):

```ts
export function createPluginContext(opts: {
  config?: Partial<PluginConfig>;
  cooldownOverrides?: Partial<Record<ErrorCategory, number>>;
  logger?: Logger;
  pluginOptions?: unknown;
} = {}): PluginContext {
  const logger = opts.logger ?? createLogger();
  const merged: PluginConfig = { ...defaultConfig, ...(opts.config ?? {}) };

  // 3-layer cooldown merge: default → opts.config → pluginOptions overrides.
  // The outer PluginConfig spread (above) does a SHALLOW merge of
  // cooldownMsByCategory, which would clobber the default inner map if
  // opts.config supplied one. Rebuild the inner map from all three layers
  // explicitly so partial overrides at any layer preserve unmentioned
  // categories from lower layers.
  const layerConfig = opts.config?.cooldownMsByCategory;
  if (layerConfig !== undefined || opts.cooldownOverrides !== undefined) {
    merged.cooldownMsByCategory = {
      ...defaultConfig.cooldownMsByCategory,
      ...(layerConfig ?? {}),
      ...(opts.cooldownOverrides ?? {}),
    };
  }

  return {
    store: new FallbackStore(),
    ttft: new TtftRegistry(),
    guard: new ExhaustionGuardRegistry(),
    chains: new Map(),
    config: merged,
    logger,
    pluginOptions: opts.pluginOptions,
  };
}
```

**2c. Update `createPluginHooks`** (`plugin-internal.ts:455-456`):

```ts
export async function createPluginHooks(opts: PluginInput, pluginOptions?: unknown): Promise<PluginHooks> {
  const logger = createLogger();
  const cooldownOverrides = extractCooldownOverrides(pluginOptions, logger);
  const ctx = createPluginContext({ pluginOptions, cooldownOverrides, logger });
  // ... rest unchanged
}
```

Note: `createLogger()` was previously called inside `createPluginContext`; moving one call site to `createPluginHooks` so the same logger flows into `extractCooldownOverrides`. `createPluginContext`'s own `opts.logger` path is preserved for tests that pass a stub.

### Change 3 — Tests

**3a. Update `test/orchestrator.test.ts:621`** — rename + new assertion + **FIX BLOCKER**: use `defaultConfig` unchanged (the existing setup explicitly constructs a local `cooldownMsByCategory` map that omits `rate_limit`, which would mask the new default and leave the test asserting 5min):

```ts
test("rate_limit uses 30min default override when not user-overridden", async () => {
  const store = new FallbackStore();
  store.sessions.get("s1").currentModel = "a/one";
  const client = new MockClient({ messages: [userMsg()] });

  // CRITICAL: use defaultConfig unchanged so the new rate_limit default
  // applies. Prior setup built a local map omitting rate_limit, which
  // would mask the fix and leave the test asserting 5min (validator blocker).
  const config = { ...defaultConfig };

  const result = await attemptFallback({
    sessionId: "s1",
    reason: "rate_limit",
    chain,
    client,
    store,
    config,
    logger: silentLogger,
    sleepMs: async () => {},
  });

  expect(result.success).toBe(true);
  const health = store.health.get("a/one" as ModelKey);
  expect(health.lastCategory).toBe("rate_limit");
  const now = Date.now();
  // 30min default — NOT the prior 5min fall-through.
  expect(health.cooldownUntil).toBeGreaterThan(now + 25 * 60_000);
  expect(health.cooldownUntil).toBeLessThan(now + 35 * 60_000);
});
```

**3b. Behavior-based plumbing tests** (per validator pass-1 + pass-2 — replace hand-wavy observation with concrete behavior; per pass-2 blocker — must initialize `state.currentModel` via `chat.message` before emitting `session.error`, otherwise orchestrator's cooldown-write path short-circuits at `plugin/src/replay/orchestrator.ts:162-185`):

```ts
describe("pluginOptions.cooldownMsByCategory plumbing", () => {
  test("user override reaches ctx.config and is applied at failure time", async () => {
    // 1. Initialize plugin with cooldownOverrides = { rate_limit: 60min }
    // 2. Drive config hook to populate ctx
    // 3. Control Date.now via mock — fix at T0
    // 4. **chat.message for session s1 with model a/one** — this initializes
    //    state.currentModel, REQUIRED for orchestrator cooldown write
    //    (without it, orchestrator.ts:184 short-circuits)
    // 5. Emit a rate_limit session.error event for s1
    // 6. Advance Date.now to T0 + 35min (past 30min default, below 60min override)
    // 7. Trigger chat.message for a new session s2, with model a/one selected
    // 8. Assert: preemptive redirect fires (model still in cooldown under override)
    //
    // If override were silently ignored, cooldown would have expired at T0+30min
    // and no redirect would fire at T0+35min.
  });

  test("additive merge preserves defaults for unmentioned categories", async () => {
    // Override rate_limit only; emit a quota_exhausted session.error; assert
    // quota_exhausted still uses default 1hr (not the override, not absent).
    // Same chat.message-before-error setup as above.
  });

  test("defensive rejection: malformed entries dropped, valid ones applied", async () => {
    const pluginOptions = {
      cooldownMsByCategory: {
        rate_limit: "30",                  // string → dropped
        not_a_category: 1000,              // unknown → dropped
        quota_exhausted: -1,               // negative → dropped
        auth_error: 0,                     // zero → accepted (no cooldown)
        ttft_timeout: Number.NaN,          // NaN → dropped
        server_error: Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY, // -Inf → dropped
        unknown_model: Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY, // +Inf → accepted (sentinel)
        unknown: 5 * 60_000,               // valid finite → accepted
        // Prototype-inherited names — must be rejected by Object.hasOwn guard:
        toString: 1000,                    // inherited → dropped
        constructor: 1000,                 // inherited → dropped
        __proto__: 1000,                   // inherited → dropped (also literal-key safety)
      },
    };
    // Assert: only auth_error, unknown_model, unknown applied.
    // Assert: warning logs emitted for the 7 dropped entries.
    // Assert: rate_limit still uses 30min default (override was rejected).
  });
});
```

**3c. Direct unit tests for exported `extractCooldownOverrides`** (per validator pass-2 warning — extractor is now exported, direct unit tests are clean):

```ts
describe("extractCooldownOverrides (direct unit)", () => {
  test.each([
    ["finite positive", 5 * 60_000, true],
    ["zero (no cooldown)", 0, true],
    ["Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY (sentinel)", Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY, true],
    ["string", "30", false],
    ["NaN", Number.NaN, false],
    ["-Infinity", Number.NEGATIVE_INFINITY, false],
    ["negative", -1, false],
    ["undefined", undefined, false],
    ["null", null, false],
    ["object", {}, false],
  ])("rate_limit=%s → accepted=%s", (label, value, accepted) => {
    const result = extractCooldownOverrides(
      { cooldownMsByCategory: { rate_limit: value } },
      silentLogger,
    );
    if (accepted) {
      expect(result?.rate_limit).toBe(value);
    } else {
      expect(result?.rate_limit).toBeUndefined();
    }
  });

  test("prototype-inherited names rejected", () => {
    const result = extractCooldownOverrides(
      { cooldownMsByCategory: { toString: 1000, constructor: 1000, __proto__: 1000 } },
      silentLogger,
    );
    expect(result).toBeUndefined();
  });
});
```

### Change 4 — Documentation cleanup (per validator pass-1)

Update three comment sites in `src/types.ts`:

- `types.ts:22-23` — clarify that `.opencode/model-routing.json` is OUT of scope for this change; the canonical user-side path is the plugin tuple option in `opencode.jsonc`/`opencode.json`.
- `types.ts:49-53` — remove or rewrite the "rate_limit thrash" warning that justifies the override mechanism (now that rate_limit IS in the default override map, the warning's premise is resolved for the default case).
- `types.ts:84-91` — drop `rate_limit` from the "transient categories" list; document the 30min default + override path.

### Change 5 — Hot-reload caveat (per validator pass-1 + refined pass-2)

Soften wording to verified operational rule (per validator pass-2 warning — prior wording exceeded evidence about config-hook reload semantics):

> Tuple options are initialization-time inputs to the plugin. Changing `cooldownMsByCategory` in `opencode.jsonc` requires an OpenCode restart to take effect. The config-hook reload path fires on OpenCode Config changes but is not guaranteed to re-invoke `pluginModule.server(input, pluginOptions)` with new tuple options; users observing cooldown changes not taking effect should restart OpenCode.

Add this note inline near `extractCooldownOverrides` call site in `createPluginHooks`.

## Decision rationale

### Why 30min for `rate_limit` default

- **MiniMax observed window**: "hour or so" per user report. 30min covers half the window — long enough to break the 5min thrash, short enough to retry within a typical work session.
- **Relative sizing**: smaller than `quota_exhausted` (1hr) because `rate_limit` semantically implies a shorter horizon than plan exhaustion.
- **Override escape hatch**: user can tune higher (e.g., 1hr for MiniMax) — that is the Bug 2 fix.

### Why additive 3-layer merge and not single-layer spread

- The outer `{...defaultConfig, ...opts.config}` PluginConfig spread is shallow — supplying `cooldownMsByCategory` in `opts.config` would clobber the entire default inner map.
- 3-layer merge (default → opts.config → pluginOptions) preserves unmentioned categories at every layer. Per validator finding.
- Critical for tests that pass partial PluginConfig shapes and for future code paths that might inject config programmatically.

### Why compile-time-exhaustive `KNOWN_CATEGORIES` (satisfies Record<ErrorCategory, true>) + prototype-safe membership (`Object.hasOwn`)

- Validator pass-1 caught: array form does not detect when an `ErrorCategory` union member is added without updating the helper.
- Validator pass-2 caught: `s in obj` accepts inherited prototype names (`toString`, `constructor`, `__proto__`).
- `satisfies Record<ErrorCategory, true>` makes the union-membership check a compile-time invariant (P33: structural over heuristic).
- `Object.hasOwn(KNOWN_CATEGORIES, s)` is the prototype-safe runtime check.
- Adding a new category in `types.ts` without updating `KNOWN_CATEGORIES` fails `tsc --noEmit`.
- Test 3b/3c explicitly verifies prototype-inherited names are rejected.

### Why `Number.POSITIVE_INFINITY` accepted programmatically but documented as non-JSON-representable

- `types.ts:55-56` documents `Infinity` as the "permanent block within process lifetime" sentinel.
- Existing test coverage at `orchestrator.test.ts:686-711` confirms Infinity works at runtime via direct PluginConfig injection.
- RFC 8259 §6 forbids Infinity in JSON numbers — users cannot express it via `opencode.jsonc`.
- Acceptance: programmatic paths (tests, future internal callers) retain Infinity. JSON paths get a documented finite fallback (e.g., 10-year ms value) until a JSON sentinel contract is added (out of scope).

### Why exported `extractCooldownOverrides`

- Validator pass-2: behavior-based integration tests via `pluginModule.server` are heavy and indirect for unit-testing edge cases like NaN, -Infinity, prototype-inherited names.
- Exporting the helper enables direct unit tests (`test.each` table-driven) covering all numeric edge cases + prototype safety.
- No leakage concern: helper is already part of the module's internal API surface; export just makes it test-visible.

### Why a typed extractor helper vs inline spread

- Helper isolates the validation logic (P33: structural validation at boundary).
- Inline spread would propagate malformed values silently.
- Helper returns `undefined` on total failure → caller falls through to `defaultConfig` cleanly.
- The `KNOWN_CATEGORIES` map co-located with the helper keeps the open `ErrorCategory` union in lockstep (P04: locality).

### Why no Go-side changes

- Go writer (`omr` binary) currently emits only `agents.<name>.fallback_models`. It does not emit cooldown config.
- Users hand-edit `opencode.jsonc` to add `cooldownMsByCategory` until Go-side support is added (separate change).
- No risk of Go writer clobbering hand-edited overrides.
- `schema-contract-check.sh` only enforces the `fallback_models` field name; new field is unaffected.

### Why no JSON schema changes in this change

- Schema design needs careful decisions: enum enforcement for `ErrorCategory`, `Infinity` JSON representation, schema file location (extend `fallback-schema.json` vs new sibling).
- All separable from the immediate bug fix.
- Type safety + defensive runtime validation + compile-time exhaustiveness + prototype-safe membership cover the correctness gap in the interim.
- Follow-up change can extend the schema without retrofitting runtime behavior.

